  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0ba3\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8 - \u0b8a\u0baa\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b88\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0bb8\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "No intention of leaving Sri Lanka - UberEats",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Uber Eates has stated that it has no plans to leave Sri Lanka.",
        "It has been reported that Uber Eates may leave Sri Lanka as the number of people involved in food consumption has declined following the rise in food prices due to rising fuel prices.",
        "However, Morning News reports that Uber Eates has stated that it has no intention of leaving Sri Lanka when questioned about this.",
        "\"We want to stand shoulder to shoulder with our colleagues in these challenging moments. We want to use our company to support the community,\" said Bhavna Jayawardena, General Manager, Uber Eates Sri Lanka."
      ],
